---
import BaseLayout from "@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout title="About — H Commerce" description="Learn how the H Commerce frontend is structured.">
  <section class="container stack-lg" style="padding-block: var(--space-8); max-width: 800px;">
    <div class="pill">About</div>
    <h1 style="margin: 0;">Frontend-first storefront</h1>
    <p class="muted">
      Astro handles routing, layouts, and SEO. React islands power carts, drawers, filters, and toasts. All catalog, category, and demo user
      records live under <code>/src/data</code> and are read through small service modules so Phase 2 can swap JSON imports for API clients without
      redesigning pages.
    </p>
    <ul class="muted" style="padding-left: 20px;">
      <li>Products and categories ship as static JSON today.</li>
      <li>Cart and wishlist persist with <code>localStorage</code> via dedicated stores.</li>
      <li>Checkout preview calls <code>order.service</code> to synthesize a demo order object.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
